Hi Parinkumar,

Thank you for the update.

The next step will be to collect the eppclient logs on a machine that has the latest client installed and the Outlook printing issue can be reproduced.

Here is the link to the EPP Support Tool (for collecting logs): https://download.endpointprotector.com/Support_files/support_tool/SupportTool_win.zip
Please find the steps below on how to run the EPP Support Tool and run it on one of the computers that have the issue.
 
Please run it as administrator and then, from the drop-down menu select Create Log File and hit execute.
Click again on the drop-down select Create DPI Log File and hit Execute.

[Inline image URL : data:image/png;base64,]

 
Once the log files are created please update the EPP Client policies and then try to reproduce the issue(allow the issue to occur for a few hours or days). The log files will be created under root C: drive.

After the issue has been reproduced a few times, from the EPP Support Tool please select Export Files and after that Create Achieve(Scroll down on the drop down menu, select it and Execute. This will copy the log files to the location where the Support Tool was installed/run and archive them.
 
This is how the archive should look like:
[Inline image URL : data:image/png;base64,]
 
And here are the files it should contain:
[Inline image URL : data:image/png;base64,]

Please send us these logs from one of the affected computers and we will continue to investigate the issue.
Thank you!

Best Regards,
Iosif Muntean| Technical Support Engineer
